Shared Whiteboard
A real-time collaborative drawing tool (like Microsoft Whiteboard or Miro) where multiple users can draw, chat, and work together on the same canvas at the same time.

What it does
Users join via a simple username
One user is the manager who approves join requests and can kick people
Everyone draws together instantly: freehand, lines, shapes (rectangle, oval, triangle), text, and erase
Built-in chat window for team communication
Manager can save/load the entire canvas as a JSON file

Built with a clean client-server architecture so everyone always sees the exact same board.
Strong distributed systems skills: sockets, multi-threading, real-time synchronization
Solid Java & JavaFX GUI development
Practical experience with JSON messaging and state management across networks
Handles concurrency and user permissions cleanly

Perfect demonstration of building a responsive, multi-user networked application.
Technologies & Skills: Java, JavaFX, Client-Server Architecture, Sockets, JSON (Jackson), Multi-threading, Real-time Collaboration
